      <p class="entitled">entitled</p>
      <longTitle>
        <p>An Act to amend the Companies Act 2014 to hold a company officer or officers acting <eol/>on behalf of a corporate body personally liable where a breach of employment law is <eol/>committed.</p>
      </longTitle>
    </preface>
    <preamble>
      <formula name="enacted">
        <p>Be it enacted by the Oireachtas as follows:</p>
      </formula>
    </preamble>
    <body>
      <section wId="section-1">
        <heading>Definitions</heading>
        <num>1.</num>
        <content>
          <p>In this Act “Principal Act” means the Companies Act 2014.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
      <section wId="section-2">
        <heading>Amendment to section 224 of Principal Act</heading>
        <num>2.</num>
        <content>
          <p>Section 224 of the Principal Act is amended by the addition of a new subsection (3)⁠—</p>
          <p>
            <mod>
              <quotedStructure>
                <subsection>
                  <num>“(3)</num>
                  <content>
                    <p>Where a breach of employment law is committed by a body corporate <eol/>or by a company officer or officers acting on behalf of a body <eol/>corporate and is determined to have been so committed, with the <eol/>consent, connivance or approval of, or to have been attributable to any <eol/>neglect on the part of, a person or persons who, when the breach was <eol/>committed was a company officer or officers of the body corporate, <eol/>then that person or persons shall be personally liable for the breach <eol/>committed.”.</p>
                  </content>
                </subsection>
              </quotedStructure>
            </mod>
          </p>
        </content>
      </section>
      <section wId="section-3">
        <heading>Short title</heading>
        <num>3.</num>
        <content>
          <p>This Act may be cited as the Companies (Amendment) Act 2016.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
    </body>
